  • distinguishedywid

    Our Wednesday morning session was all about service.  The Distinguished Young Women of Idaho Service Coordinator Jana Hill put together an event where we got to work with two great organizations.  

    Avrey Hendrix of the Idaho Period Project spoke to the girls about her organization. Then we were able to help put together kits that her organization will distribute to girls in Idaho.  

    Then we heard from Jacque Burt from the Idaho Foster and Adoptive Association about their mission. The girls were able to pack 37 diaper bags for babies entering the foster system.   

    All of the items that were used to pack the kits for the Idaho Period Project and the diaper bags for the foster babies were donated within all of the local communities in Idaho that these girls represent. They arrived here on Sunday with loads of items for the kids and the diaper bags and other items that will be donated to The Village which also supports Idaho foster families.

    Working with us today were Sarah, Sydney, and Heather with Good 2 Go and The Hall  Foundation. We so appreciate their help, and that their servant hearts!

    We worked on a little bit of interview prep, and then our lunch was provided by the local program in Madison!

    19w
